1
00:00:45,129 --> 00:00:53,093
"Who am I to you?"

2
00:00:54,161 --> 00:01:01,124
"Who am I to you?"

3
00:01:16,573 --> 00:01:23,536
"My eyes are restless!"

4
00:01:24,495 --> 00:01:31,458
"This is the effect of love!"

5
00:01:32,390 --> 00:01:39,354
"Can't be mum, all I can say is that..."

6
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:48,196
"...who am I to you?"

7
00:01:48,227 --> 00:01:56,019
"Who am I to you?"

8
00:02:04,103 --> 00:02:11,066
"I had to restrain myself, my love."

9
00:02:11,977 --> 00:02:18,940
"Ultimately, I had to say it."

10
00:02:19,836 --> 00:02:26,799
"In my dreams... why do you come?"

11
00:02:27,765 --> 00:02:34,769
"Who am I to you?"

12
00:02:35,676 --> 00:02:43,496
"Who am I to you?"

13
00:02:51,674 --> 00:02:58,955
"My eyes are restless!"

14
00:02:59,470 --> 00:03:06,361
"This is the effect of love!"

15
00:03:07,384 --> 00:03:14,111
"I'm sort of lost...
please don't ask me..."

16
00:03:15,287 --> 00:03:22,250
"...who am I to you?"

17
00:03:23,195 --> 00:03:30,064
"Who am I to you?"

18
00:03:39,036 --> 00:03:45,999
"How should I tell you
the feelings in my heart?"

19
00:03:46,892 --> 00:03:54,057
"Try to read my face sometimes."

20
00:03:54,805 --> 00:04:01,455
"You may call it my shyness!"

21
00:04:02,710 --> 00:04:09,673
"Who am I to you?"

22
00:04:10,599 --> 00:04:17,517
"Who am I to you?"

23
00:04:18,505 --> 00:04:25,468
"Who am I to you?"

24
00:04:36,791 --> 00:04:40,573
COMMENTATOR: We welcome all
the spectators to 'Prem Nivas'.

25
00:04:44,253 --> 00:04:44,979
Hello!

26
00:04:45,198 --> 00:04:49,799
- Greetings to one and all from Lalloo Prasad!

27
00:04:49,893 --> 00:04:51,907
The match is about to begin
in a short while from now.

28
00:04:51,932 --> 00:04:54,853
I will be giving the live commentary.

29
00:04:55,042 --> 00:04:58,156
The sky is absolutely clear...
there are a few clouds.

30
00:04:58,463 --> 00:05:03,205
The umpire has inspected the pitch
and is about to take his place.

31
00:05:10,039 --> 00:05:12,007
The batsman is ready. Fielders, be alert.

32
00:05:12,586 --> 00:05:17,312
Presenting to you, one who bowls
at a speed faster than the wind!

33
00:05:26,828 --> 00:05:28,687
I will hit him for a 6,
off the first ball itself.

34
00:05:33,045 --> 00:05:35,013
Should I hit him for a 4 or a 6?

35
00:05:36,992 --> 00:05:38,032
Go, Lalloo Prasad!

36
00:05:39,211 --> 00:05:39,859
How's that?

37
00:05:42,742 --> 00:05:44,828
Hey Lalloo,
you are always out to the first ball!

38
00:05:47,149 --> 00:05:50,593
- I just gave the bowler a chance.
- What did you say?

39
00:05:50,618 --> 00:05:53,273
- It's your turn to bat.
- No, it's my turn. I will play too.

40
00:05:53,298 --> 00:05:57,397
You must be aware as to what
happened when Rita last came to bat.

41
00:05:57,422 --> 00:05:58,937
She broke her leg.

42
00:06:00,439 --> 00:06:01,304
Oh, shut up!

43
00:06:01,821 --> 00:06:03,875
Prem will coach me this time.
Won't you, Prem?

44
00:06:03,929 --> 00:06:07,984
Will I coach you?
Go and field on the boundary line.

45
00:06:08,531 --> 00:06:10,187
You always ask me to field.

46
00:06:10,212 --> 00:06:12,009
It's similar to what you've been doing
to hook Prem for all these years.

47
00:06:12,071 --> 00:06:12,407
What?

48
00:06:12,465 --> 00:06:14,320
You will field, while Prem will bat.

49
00:06:14,345 --> 00:06:16,437
- You will go and bowl.
- Yes, sir.

50
00:06:16,852 --> 00:06:18,399
LALLOO: Kapil Dev, come to my rescue!

51
00:06:18,547 --> 00:06:20,117
Protect yourself from my attack, Prem.

52
00:06:20,142 --> 00:06:22,359
Here comes Lalloo with his googly.

53
00:06:22,508 --> 00:06:23,992
Hey!

54
00:06:25,594 --> 00:06:27,328
LALLOO: Rita, catch the ball.

55
00:06:33,929 --> 00:06:37,067
BHAGVANTI: I'm dead. I'm dead.
- Don't utter inauspicious things.

56
00:06:37,092 --> 00:06:38,539
My back is broken.

57
00:06:39,227 --> 00:06:42,226
- I'm sorry, auntie!
- You fool, what are you doing here?

58
00:06:42,251 --> 00:06:42,726
Oh...

59
00:06:42,751 --> 00:06:44,915
Auntie, she had come here
to learn to play cricket.

60
00:06:44,940 --> 00:06:49,133
This game of cricket
is becoming a nuisance.

61
00:06:49,852 --> 00:06:52,461
- Kids will always play!
- Quiet!

62
00:06:52,509 --> 00:06:54,187
Greetings, auntie!

63
00:06:54,322 --> 00:06:58,305
How many times have I told
you not to call me auntie?

64
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:04,688
Not only humans, but dogs too
are pampered here in this house.

65
00:07:04,813 --> 00:07:06,984
Why are you staring at me? Come with me.

66
00:07:07,398 --> 00:07:11,445
- I'm dead!
- Uncle, why is auntie in such a haste?

67
00:07:11,570 --> 00:07:17,545
She's come to talk to your uncle
about your brother, Rajesh's wedding.

68
00:07:17,625 --> 00:07:22,426
Honestly speaking, Rajesh is worth
every good word spoken about him!

69
00:07:23,078 --> 00:07:24,826
Not only me,
but everybody is of the same opinion.

70
00:07:25,147 --> 00:07:28,953
It's not a joke to manage this
big business at such young age!

71
00:07:29,117 --> 00:07:30,601
- What do you say?
- Perfect!

72
00:07:30,696 --> 00:07:33,039
You have to think about his wedding now.

73
00:07:33,696 --> 00:07:35,493
Tell me, if you know of any good girl.

74
00:07:35,523 --> 00:07:38,140
- I have seen the girl.
- Is that so?

75
00:07:38,208 --> 00:07:42,203
You have met my brother from Delhi,
Rita's dad, haven't you? - Yes.

76
00:07:42,296 --> 00:07:45,484
I was referring to his elder daughter,
that's Rita's elder sister, Sweetie.

77
00:07:45,524 --> 00:07:48,883
Sweetie has always been with him
in Delhi and Rita's been with me.

78
00:07:49,027 --> 00:07:52,265
Sweetie is a very beautiful,
understanding and decent girl!

79
00:07:52,296 --> 00:07:54,414
- Isn't that so?
- Yes. She's failed in B.A.

80
00:07:55,008 --> 00:07:56,976
She thinks in terms of
the present generation.

81
00:07:57,380 --> 00:07:59,774
She's already had a couple of
broken engagements. Isn't that so?

82
00:08:00,297 --> 00:08:04,084
So what? Think about the big family.
Their business is worth millions.

83
00:08:04,109 --> 00:08:05,594
The wedding will be a pompous one.

84
00:08:05,619 --> 00:08:07,812
She'll bring along something
worthwhile as dowry, too.

85
00:08:08,008 --> 00:08:11,078
But you won't understand
these norms of life!

86
00:08:11,128 --> 00:08:12,961
After all,
you are a professor at the college.

87
00:08:13,188 --> 00:08:16,477
If you agree,
I will inform my brother accordingly.

88
00:08:16,828 --> 00:08:20,219
Rita, it's time for our kitty party.
Let's go!

89
00:08:20,657 --> 00:08:22,836
- We're leaving.
- Thanks!

90
00:08:22,914 --> 00:08:24,937
- What did you say?
- Nothing.

91
00:08:25,217 --> 00:08:26,576
- I'll leave, brother.
- Okay!

92
00:08:26,601 --> 00:08:28,407
Come on. You're quite a hog.

93
00:08:30,208 --> 00:08:33,828
Wealth is all that she thinks of!

94
00:08:34,371 --> 00:08:36,168
We don't want her rich brother's daughter.

95
00:08:37,375 --> 00:08:39,953
What we want is a down-to-earth
and a lovely daughter-in-law!

96
00:08:40,630 --> 00:08:43,071
One who will bless this
house with her love and care!

97
00:08:44,101 --> 00:08:47,453
You have brought up this
house with so much love!

98
00:08:47,862 --> 00:08:51,211
Rajesh and Prem were so small
when sister and her husband died.

99
00:08:52,179 --> 00:08:55,313
You abandoned your studies too
to look after these children.

100
00:08:55,465 --> 00:08:57,016
You started off with a small job.

101
00:08:57,777 --> 00:09:00,571
For their future,
you only thought of hard work as your goal.

102
00:09:01,102 --> 00:09:02,466
You didn't marry too!

103
00:09:03,570 --> 00:09:05,453
You've brought up these
children with such good values!

104
00:09:05,774 --> 00:09:07,344
That's the reason for Rajesh's success.

105
00:09:07,391 --> 00:09:09,188
Prem too has stood first
at the MBA exams this year.

106
00:09:09,305 --> 00:09:09,797
Am I right?

107
00:09:10,922 --> 00:09:13,273
Brother, I have seen a girl for Rajesh.

108
00:09:13,752 --> 00:09:16,179
Sometime back,
I had gone to Pune for a conference.

109
00:09:16,367 --> 00:09:18,852
I met Professor S. S.
Chowdhury over there.

110
00:09:19,070 --> 00:09:22,242
- Would that be Prof. Siddharth Chowdhury?
- Do you know him?

111
00:09:22,421 --> 00:09:25,352
We've studied in the same college.
We were very good friends.

112
00:09:25,377 --> 00:09:27,976
I met his elder daughter over there.

113
00:09:28,373 --> 00:09:31,446
Just saw her for once, and she's
made a home for herself in my heart!

114
00:09:31,765 --> 00:09:34,336
I liked her so much that I
brought her photograph too.

115
00:09:35,492 --> 00:09:38,641
Her name is Pooja. She's passed B.A.
Very sweet in nature!

116
00:09:39,311 --> 00:09:41,321
- They'll make a good pair.
- I agree!

117
00:09:41,492 --> 00:09:44,908
Professor has gone on a pilgrimage
with his family to Ramtekdi.

118
00:09:45,382 --> 00:09:47,999
As soon as he returns, we'll pay him a
visit. It's just a trip of 3-4 hours.

119
00:09:48,299 --> 00:09:51,844
All that's required is for them to like
each other. - That's the main problem.

120
00:09:52,004 --> 00:09:54,320
Whenever I talk about marriage to
Rajesh, he ignores it.

121
00:09:54,446 --> 00:09:56,359
How can we make the two of them meet?

122
00:09:56,494 --> 00:09:58,788
There is a way.
Why don't we go to Ramtekdi too?

123
00:09:58,813 --> 00:10:00,249
It would be a combination of
a holiday and a pilgrimage.

124
00:10:00,250 --> 00:10:01,055
And also the selection of sister-in-law.

125
00:10:01,089 --> 00:10:02,281
- Great!
- Very good idea!

126
00:10:02,327 --> 00:10:05,367
But brother shouldn't be aware of this plan.
Everyone should be alert.

127
00:10:05,414 --> 00:10:06,430
It's a top secret!

128
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:12,883
Big brother is here. Come on, uncle.

129
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:17,789
So you're back, Rajesh.
Your meeting took a long time today!

130
00:10:17,976 --> 00:10:19,391
What did the foreign collaborators say?

131
00:10:19,424 --> 00:10:23,453
We had a detailed discussion.
They'll study our report now.

132
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:26,053
Uncle, if everything works out properly...

133
00:10:26,078 --> 00:10:29,804
...like you said, this factory will be
the first of its kind in this country!

134
00:10:30,273 --> 00:10:35,008
Prem, your brother is setting up
such a big factory to launch you.

135
00:10:35,446 --> 00:10:37,179
LALLOO: Big brother, the food is ready.

136
00:10:37,820 --> 00:10:42,359
Hey, there's a feast out here!
Is it some special occasion?

137
00:10:42,696 --> 00:10:46,711
- Actually, big brother...
- Well, we all are very happy today.

138
00:10:46,985 --> 00:10:47,383
Happy?

139
00:10:47,481 --> 00:10:50,319
Well, big brother, we have decided
to go to Ramtekdi for our holidays.

140
00:10:50,609 --> 00:10:54,409
Ramtekdi? But uncle, you were
insisting on going to a hill station.

141
00:10:55,517 --> 00:11:00,412
Ramtekdi is a very holy place.
My uncle and aunt go there every year.

142
00:11:00,437 --> 00:11:02,569
- They make vows too!
- The program is fixed.

143
00:11:03,682 --> 00:11:06,139
This time we'll take that
new dress of yours, too.

144
00:11:06,493 --> 00:11:08,498
- Why is it needed over there?
- Why not?!

145
00:11:08,912 --> 00:11:10,310
You never know...

146
00:11:11,061 --> 00:11:13,725
- What did he say, uncle?
- I didn't hear.

147
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:17,444
We don't interfere in such matters.
Chameli, let's get some food.

148
00:11:25,685 --> 00:11:27,911
Strange! Nobody is telling me anything.

149
00:11:29,076 --> 00:11:33,530
What should we tell you, brother...
as to what we will get at Ramtekdi.

150
00:12:13,043 --> 00:12:14,381
Hurry up, dad!

151
00:12:14,434 --> 00:12:18,550
Mom will be mad, if she catches you
doing this experiment in the kitchen.

152
00:12:18,575 --> 00:12:21,060
Let her be angry. I'm not afraid of her.

153
00:12:21,286 --> 00:12:24,987
If she notices these sweets,
she'll be tempted to break her fast.

154
00:12:25,050 --> 00:12:25,940
PROF. CHOWDHURY: Are you listening?

155
00:12:25,965 --> 00:12:28,419
- What is it?
- It's not me, but mom.

156
00:12:46,232 --> 00:12:49,498
PROF. CHOWDHURY: Very angrily he
said, "You foolish man!"

157
00:12:49,701 --> 00:12:52,966
Seeing everybody scared
and Sita restless...

158
00:12:53,065 --> 00:12:55,208
- Who broke the jar?
- What?

159
00:12:57,060 --> 00:12:58,388
Who broke the jar?

160
00:12:58,771 --> 00:13:02,021
Pooja, when Lord Rama
broke Lord Shiva's bow...

161
00:13:02,052 --> 00:13:05,708
...Parshurama very angrily asked
as to who had broken the bow.

162
00:13:05,866 --> 00:13:09,482
Lord Rama, with all
simplicity and love replied...

163
00:13:09,887 --> 00:13:14,863
"''O God, someone from your slaves
must have broken Lord Shiva's bow."

164
00:13:14,928 --> 00:13:17,980
Have some shame. We've got two grown
up girls. What will they think?

165
00:13:18,019 --> 00:13:20,871
What will they think?
Did I say something wrong, my love?

166
00:13:20,997 --> 00:13:23,253
I didn't say anything wrong. I was just...

167
00:13:23,285 --> 00:13:25,480
It's difficult for both
of us to win against you.

168
00:13:25,683 --> 00:13:27,620
- If anyone can win against you, it will be...
- Nisha!

169
00:13:35,769 --> 00:13:36,269
MAN: Hey...

170
00:13:36,386 --> 00:13:37,870
Good morning, manager uncle!

171
00:13:46,728 --> 00:13:50,518
Devil! You always come
like an express train!

172
00:13:51,274 --> 00:13:53,986
Dad has sent the books from the
library and has said thanks.

173
00:13:54,063 --> 00:13:54,617
Okay!

174
00:13:57,282 --> 00:14:03,431
- Brother, your bill?
- Here's the bill. You remove the books.

175
00:14:03,744 --> 00:14:06,541
- Then, I'll leave...
- Okay, that's also fine.

176
00:14:06,845 --> 00:14:08,416
Nisha child,
will you do me a small favour?

177
00:14:08,515 --> 00:14:12,064
Will you add this up by the time
we come back from the storeroom?

178
00:14:12,089 --> 00:14:15,072
- Sure!
- Very good! But, listen...

179
00:14:15,299 --> 00:14:16,806
...don't indulge in any mischief.

180
00:14:18,752 --> 00:14:21,384
Come on, now. What are you staring at?

181
00:14:50,596 --> 00:14:51,299
Excuse me!

182
00:14:52,822 --> 00:14:54,611
Is this Ram Narayan guesthouse?

183
00:14:56,095 --> 00:15:00,736
Didn't you read the board outside?
Where was I?!

184
00:15:01,041 --> 00:15:04,533
- 75 and 9...
- 84!

185
00:15:15,830 --> 00:15:20,345
What is it? - Can you tell me
which room Prof. Chowdhury is in?

186
00:15:21,734 --> 00:15:24,892
- Why?
- Well... I had some work.

187
00:15:26,903 --> 00:15:28,025
- I understood.
- What?

188
00:15:28,893 --> 00:15:30,134
- Stand up!
- Pardon?

189
00:15:30,525 --> 00:15:34,744
Stand up! You people don't
study the whole year...

190
00:15:34,774 --> 00:15:35,150
What?

191
00:15:35,277 --> 00:15:39,101
Yes, you don't study the whole year
and then panic at the time of exams.

192
00:15:39,150 --> 00:15:41,251
And now, you've come here
to enhance your marks.

193
00:15:41,533 --> 00:15:43,330
You better enhance the number
of your glasses, madam!

194
00:15:43,448 --> 00:15:46,064
Wonder what you think of yourself
after sitting on the manager's chair!

195
00:15:46,089 --> 00:15:47,307
- Well...
- POOJA: Nisha!

196
00:15:47,775 --> 00:15:48,658
Oh, God!

197
00:16:00,775 --> 00:16:02,408
POOJA: Nisha... - I'm over here, sister.

198
00:16:08,346 --> 00:16:13,447
You're sitting here!
Mom is waiting for you out there.

199
00:16:13,775 --> 00:16:16,650
- What were you doing?
- Well, I was... I was...

200
00:16:20,705 --> 00:16:23,541
Welcome! - Uncle,
you proceed while I keep the baggage.

201
00:16:23,566 --> 00:16:25,122
- Okay, dear!
- Come, let's go!

202
00:16:27,010 --> 00:16:29,516
You were asking for Prof.
Chowdhury, right?

203
00:16:29,626 --> 00:16:31,518
These are his daughters, Pooja and Nisha.

204
00:16:31,658 --> 00:16:35,637
Pooja child, he is Mr. Kailashnath.
He's your dad's pal.

205
00:16:35,893 --> 00:16:37,770
- Greetings!
- Greetings!

206
00:16:37,854 --> 00:16:40,392
- He wants to meet the professor.
- Please, come.

207
00:16:41,463 --> 00:16:42,510
I'll take your leave.

208
00:16:44,150 --> 00:16:45,971
Oh, manager uncle...

209
00:16:47,260 --> 00:16:48,814
Take this. I've calculated it.

210
00:16:48,936 --> 00:16:52,697
You have? That's great!
Here's your reward.

211
00:16:54,906 --> 00:16:55,572
Thank you!

212
00:16:56,206 --> 00:16:59,236
Manager, you please recalculate.

213
00:16:59,439 --> 00:17:02,564
People say that beautiful girls
are always wrong at calculating.

214
00:17:03,510 --> 00:17:06,479
- What did you say?
- Do you eat chocolates, Miss Nisha?

215
00:17:07,322 --> 00:17:08,223
Don't mention my name.

216
00:17:11,822 --> 00:17:15,408
These snacks taste great, professor!

217
00:17:15,494 --> 00:17:20,134
Have it with this 'chutney' and you
will forget the famous 'Mathura snacks'.

218
00:17:20,159 --> 00:17:21,089
Mr. Siddharth!

219
00:17:24,128 --> 00:17:25,972
Hey... Kai...

220
00:17:26,049 --> 00:17:30,830
- Kailashnath! What a plesant surprise! Wow!

221
00:17:31,343 --> 00:17:35,048
- My younger nephew, Prem.
- May you live long, child!

222
00:17:35,291 --> 00:17:37,775
- Your uncle has lost a bet.
- Which one?

223
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:40,673
He had said that only I would go
bald, but he has lost his hair too.

224
00:17:40,698 --> 00:17:41,778
Have a look!

225
00:17:42,877 --> 00:17:44,416
Hello, see who has come...

226
00:17:48,002 --> 00:17:50,658
- Greetings! Recognize me?
- How are you?

227
00:17:50,689 --> 00:17:53,658
He has to be fine. After all,
he's one of the top industrialists!

228
00:17:54,056 --> 00:17:54,729
Come and have a seat.

229
00:17:56,602 --> 00:18:00,166
Truly, whenever I read about you
in the papers, I feel very proud!

230
00:18:00,572 --> 00:18:01,666
It's all right!

231
00:18:02,369 --> 00:18:05,338
Prem, you may not be aware about
the history of the three of us.

232
00:18:05,616 --> 00:18:09,330
We were in college together and we
had a lot of fun. Right, Kailashnath?

233
00:18:10,408 --> 00:18:11,885
Keep it here.

234
00:18:12,267 --> 00:18:14,603
- You've already met my daughters, right?
- Yes.

235
00:18:17,033 --> 00:18:19,009
Do you come here every year?

236
00:18:20,354 --> 00:18:21,877
I've come this year with
a very special mission.

237
00:18:22,205 --> 00:18:22,713
Really?

238
00:18:22,955 --> 00:18:26,314
I'd like my nephew Rajesh to get
married to your elder daughter.

239
00:18:26,954 --> 00:18:27,540
PROF. CHOWDHURY: Pooja?

240
00:18:28,619 --> 00:18:29,080
MR. KAILASHNATH: Yes.

241
00:18:29,275 --> 00:18:30,979
That's if you don't have any objections.

242
00:18:32,012 --> 00:18:35,376
Objection? What are you talking?
After all, he's your nephew!

243
00:18:35,401 --> 00:18:38,979
Still... Rajesh has come with us.
You meet him, once.

244
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:40,893
- Go and call brother.
- You mean...

245
00:18:41,509 --> 00:18:42,876
Yes! Go, right ahead.

246
00:18:45,385 --> 00:18:46,244
Kailashnath!

247
00:18:48,192 --> 00:18:52,541
- Thanks!
- Professor, I should be thanking you.

248
00:18:53,812 --> 00:18:57,103
God has given me everything!
The love of these children...

249
00:18:57,638 --> 00:19:00,666
...a big business empire...
but the house seems barren!

250
00:19:01,510 --> 00:19:03,541
Rajesh has had his share
of motherly love...

251
00:19:04,177 --> 00:19:07,220
...but Prem has been
deprived of that love.

252
00:19:15,236 --> 00:19:17,830
- Come on, brother!
- Come in, Rajesh.

253
00:19:18,301 --> 00:19:19,951
The Professor... and his wife.

254
00:19:19,989 --> 00:19:22,012
- Greetings! Please, sit...
- Have a seat, child.

255
00:19:38,342 --> 00:19:40,803
Apart from your work,
what are your other hobbies?

256
00:19:41,213 --> 00:19:44,182
Brother paints very well.
Isn't that right, brother?

257
00:19:44,522 --> 00:19:46,350
- Is that so?
- Just a little bit.

258
00:19:46,640 --> 00:19:49,615
Pooja paints well too, isn't that so?

259
00:19:49,725 --> 00:19:50,256
Pooja...

260
00:19:52,271 --> 00:19:52,912
Go!

261
00:19:53,819 --> 00:19:57,389
Yes, dad. - Show Rajesh that painting
of the temple that you're doing.

262
00:19:58,483 --> 00:20:01,545
Brother, let's go and see the painting.
We'll just be back, uncle.

263
00:20:01,643 --> 00:20:03,975
Come on brother,
let's have a look at the painting.

264
00:20:09,494 --> 00:20:11,462
- Where are you going?
- How does it concern you?

265
00:20:12,069 --> 00:20:16,342
You let them talk. You can talk to me.

266
00:20:17,061 --> 00:20:18,481
- What should I talk to you?
- Why?

267
00:20:19,264 --> 00:20:21,694
Are you still angry with me?

268
00:20:22,170 --> 00:20:22,639
Miss Nisha...

269
00:20:23,386 --> 00:20:24,516
Don't mention my name.

270
00:20:27,186 --> 00:20:28,639
- Mom...
- Dad...

271
00:20:32,979 --> 00:20:34,967
- It's a very nice painting!
- Thank you.

272
00:20:38,922 --> 00:20:40,936
You paint too, don't you?

273
00:20:41,334 --> 00:20:41,865
Yes.

274
00:20:42,530 --> 00:20:46,225
I do paint but... not so beautiful!

275
00:21:00,383 --> 00:21:00,897
Give it to me.

276
00:21:08,006 --> 00:21:09,139
Brother, did you like the painting?

277
00:21:11,009 --> 00:21:12,982
I've been noticing since the afternoon.

278
00:21:13,294 --> 00:21:14,584
You've been asking me the same
question every 15 minutes.

279
00:21:15,217 --> 00:21:16,467
- What's the matter?
- Matter?

280
00:21:17,385 --> 00:21:19,889
Well, I will go and get you some nice tea.

281
00:21:20,881 --> 00:21:21,426
Wait!

282
00:21:24,381 --> 00:21:25,952
Tell me, what is the truth?

283
00:21:26,006 --> 00:21:27,842
Promise me that you will neither scold
me, nor will you beat me.

284
00:21:27,928 --> 00:21:29,389
- Promise?
- Yes, it's a promise.

285
00:21:30,646 --> 00:21:31,646
Did you like the painting?

286
00:21:32,225 --> 00:21:32,748
Yes.

287
00:21:33,153 --> 00:21:35,959
- Did you like the colors of the painting?
- Yes.

288
00:21:36,983 --> 00:21:38,553
Did you like the one who did the painting?

289
00:21:41,998 --> 00:21:46,732
That's great! We had brought
you here to hear this. Congrats!

290
00:21:47,490 --> 00:21:49,458
- Uncle...
- You wait!

291
00:21:49,502 --> 00:21:51,779
Uncle, brother's life is made.

292
00:21:52,006 --> 00:21:52,491
Prem!

293
00:21:53,108 --> 00:21:54,194
Greetings, priest!

294
00:21:56,094 --> 00:21:58,201
- Sister-in-law, save me!

295
00:22:17,677 --> 00:22:22,637
"You're great Lord...
what a pair you have created!"

296
00:22:24,279 --> 00:22:29,161
"Congratulations to my
brother and sister-in-law!"

297
00:22:30,810 --> 00:22:34,019
"More than any other
ritual in this world..."

298
00:22:34,044 --> 00:22:36,684
"...the relation of hearts
is the most important!"

299
00:22:37,318 --> 00:22:42,372
"Thanks to you, this event has
seen the light of the day."

300
00:22:43,677 --> 00:22:48,637
"Congratulations to my
sister and brother-in-law!"

301
00:22:50,279 --> 00:22:53,543
"More than any other
ritual in this world..."

302
00:22:53,568 --> 00:22:56,366
"...the relation of hearts
is the most important!"

303
00:22:56,685 --> 00:23:02,075
- "You're great Lord!"
- "You're great Lord!"

304
00:23:03,146 --> 00:23:06,115
"You're great Lord!"

305
00:23:28,828 --> 00:23:34,950
"My brother, who is sitting so quietly."

306
00:23:35,303 --> 00:23:40,428
"Sister-in-law,
have a look at his stubborn posture."

307
00:23:41,928 --> 00:23:43,928
"But, he is a very good guy."

308
00:23:45,209 --> 00:23:48,411
"He is a very good guy,
but a bit naughty."

309
00:23:48,436 --> 00:23:51,873
"You're the only one
that he has fallen for!"

310
00:23:52,092 --> 00:23:57,352
"My sister is acting tough now!"

311
00:23:58,577 --> 00:24:03,428
"Congratulations to my
brother and sister-in-law!"

312
00:24:05,084 --> 00:24:08,333
"More than any other
ritual in this world..."

313
00:24:08,358 --> 00:24:11,389
"...the relation of hearts
is the most important!"

314
00:24:11,498 --> 00:24:17,248
- "You're great, Lord!"
- "You're great, Lord!"

315
00:24:17,944 --> 00:24:20,913
"You're great, Lord!"

316
00:24:43,667 --> 00:24:49,675
"Brother-in-law, for your sake..."

317
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:55,621
"...my sister has prayed a lot!"

318
00:24:56,597 --> 00:25:01,634
"She's been to the temples..."
"She's been to the temples..."

319
00:25:01,659 --> 00:25:03,253
"...prayed day and night!"

320
00:25:03,278 --> 00:25:06,869
"She's been invoking
Almighty all the time"

321
00:25:06,901 --> 00:25:12,232
"I've got a daughter-in-law
as I had desired!"

322
00:25:13,451 --> 00:25:18,529
"Congratulations to my
sister and brother-in-law!"

323
00:25:19,989 --> 00:25:23,254
"More than any other
ritual in this world..."

324
00:25:23,279 --> 00:25:26,068
"...the relation of hearts
is the most important!"

325
00:25:26,366 --> 00:25:32,193
- "You're great, Lord!"
- "You're great, Lord!"

326
00:25:32,911 --> 00:25:35,840
"You're great, Lord!"

327
00:26:00,199 --> 00:26:02,058
Tuffy... Tuffy... Tuffy...

328
00:26:02,432 --> 00:26:05,401
That's a nice garland you've
brought, Tuffy!

329
00:26:05,648 --> 00:26:08,596
Tuffy too knows that this evening,
folks from brother's in-law's place...

330
00:26:08,621 --> 00:26:11,151
...are coming with the ritual offerings.

331
00:26:11,190 --> 00:26:13,932
There shouldn't be anything amiss
in welcoming them. Right, Tuffy?

332
00:26:14,002 --> 00:26:14,682
Great!

333
00:26:15,339 --> 00:26:19,362
- Big brother, is she coming too?
- I'll just be back, uncle.

334
00:26:20,464 --> 00:26:23,112
- What happened?
- You'll always stay a fool!

335
00:26:23,137 --> 00:26:23,566
Why?

336
00:26:23,620 --> 00:26:26,800
Uncle, does the girl come
over before the wedding?

337
00:26:27,191 --> 00:26:29,667
How do I know? We aren't married as yet.

338
00:26:32,668 --> 00:26:33,324
Brother!

339
00:26:34,214 --> 00:26:34,621
Yes?

340
00:26:35,354 --> 00:26:35,925
Come!

341
00:26:36,629 --> 00:26:39,144
You are needed desperately
down here in the hall.

342
00:26:39,582 --> 00:26:40,808
The doctor has come, too.

343
00:26:41,082 --> 00:26:42,644
What does he think of himself?!

344
00:26:42,784 --> 00:26:44,883
Let him come. I'll take care of him.

345
00:26:45,173 --> 00:26:47,141
- Greetings, doctor.
- Greetings!

346
00:26:47,212 --> 00:26:49,415
What's the matter? Why are you so angry?

347
00:26:49,454 --> 00:26:51,610
Are you asking me?

348
00:26:52,454 --> 00:26:55,246
You ask him that question.

349
00:26:55,728 --> 00:26:57,743
He confirmed Rajesh's marriage,
chose the daughter-in-law.

350
00:26:57,825 --> 00:26:59,446
I get the news today.

351
00:26:59,759 --> 00:27:00,711
- Doctor...
- What?!

352
00:27:01,664 --> 00:27:03,407
What is it? I don't want it.

353
00:27:03,469 --> 00:27:06,196
I'm very angry today.
I will neither eat, nor drink today.

354
00:27:06,298 --> 00:27:09,118
I'm leaving. Congratulations!
Goodbye. Move aside!

355
00:27:10,579 --> 00:27:13,680
The photo of my daughter-in-law
is on the table.

356
00:27:19,938 --> 00:27:20,852
How did you like daughter-in-law?

357
00:27:22,313 --> 00:27:22,892
Pal...

358
00:27:23,899 --> 00:27:25,657
Her simplicity reminds me of a poem.

359
00:27:25,673 --> 00:27:29,476
Sit down. Doctor will recite a poem.

360
00:27:29,501 --> 00:27:31,836
- It goes something like this...
- Wow, wow...

361
00:27:31,861 --> 00:27:33,524
Let me start the poem.

362
00:27:34,524 --> 00:27:37,493
'I've turned into a photo
after looking at the photo...

363
00:27:37,587 --> 00:27:38,353
Wow!

364
00:27:38,387 --> 00:27:41,172
'I've turned into a photo
after looking at the photo...

365
00:27:41,242 --> 00:27:43,790
...l'm so jealous of my
friend's good fortune.'

366
00:27:43,815 --> 00:27:45,212
Wow, wow!

367
00:27:45,290 --> 00:27:49,836
Have a look!
He told me that he is very angry.

368
00:27:50,032 --> 00:27:51,517
Told me not to talk to anyone.

369
00:27:51,563 --> 00:27:55,399
One look at daughter-in-law's
photo and your anger vanished!

370
00:27:56,376 --> 00:27:57,954
Welcome, sister-in-law!

371
00:27:58,172 --> 00:28:02,132
I can understand that you
are a heart specialist...

372
00:28:02,157 --> 00:28:03,139
...and sister-in-law
is a child specialist.

373
00:28:03,509 --> 00:28:07,609
What I can't understand is this
combination of a doctor and a poet.

374
00:28:07,634 --> 00:28:11,407
That's something he has
taken very seriously.

375
00:28:11,535 --> 00:28:13,500
Uncle, why do you indulge in this poetry?

376
00:28:13,806 --> 00:28:16,604
Poetry in its truest form
is always in front of you!

377
00:28:17,384 --> 00:28:20,374
What did you say? What did you say?

378
00:28:20,399 --> 00:28:27,362
Wait! Did you hear that?
This younger one talks a lot these days.

379
00:28:27,767 --> 00:28:31,912
Shall we get you married
too, along with your brother?

380
00:28:31,937 --> 00:28:36,602
- Auntie, why delay something good?
- Shameless!

381
00:28:37,532 --> 00:28:38,735
- Hi!
- Hi!

382
00:28:39,938 --> 00:28:41,782
I heard doctor auntie's talks.

383
00:28:42,235 --> 00:28:44,922
It's your turn to search for a bride.

384
00:28:45,470 --> 00:28:47,407
I'm just coming. Somebody is calling me.

385
00:28:47,469 --> 00:28:48,571
- Hi!
- Oh, no!

386
00:28:48,915 --> 00:28:51,938
Whenever I want to talk to you,
somebody always calls for you.

387
00:28:52,462 --> 00:28:54,852
But I know very well how
to win over your heart.

388
00:28:55,087 --> 00:28:57,315
The formula to make
sweets in half an hour.

389
00:28:57,456 --> 00:29:01,883
First of all, the utensil... where's it?

390
00:29:02,024 --> 00:29:02,750
Utensil...

391
00:29:03,529 --> 00:29:04,740
Oh, no!

392
00:29:05,540 --> 00:29:07,102
Stupid, I'm hurt.

393
00:29:07,239 --> 00:29:09,383
How could I know that
you were standing here?

394
00:29:09,616 --> 00:29:11,461
- Quiet! Give me the utensil.
- Utensil...

395
00:29:12,305 --> 00:29:14,891
By the way, baby, what are you doing here?

396
00:29:14,969 --> 00:29:19,571
- I'm making sweets.
- So you're making sweets for Prem!

397
00:29:19,677 --> 00:29:21,219
Are you making it as per this book?

398
00:29:21,281 --> 00:29:22,218
- Don't touch!
- Don't touch.

399
00:29:22,545 --> 00:29:25,664
Just answer whatever I ask of you.

400
00:29:26,136 --> 00:29:27,657
- Where's the semolina?
- It's over there.

401
00:29:27,952 --> 00:29:29,688
- Butter?
- Right next to it.

402
00:29:31,298 --> 00:29:33,266
- Sugar?
- In that jar.

403
00:29:36,298 --> 00:29:37,337
- Baby, you are...
- Stupid!

404
00:29:38,704 --> 00:29:39,259
Listen!

405
00:29:39,301 --> 00:29:42,277
- What happened?
- She brought salt instead of sugar.

406
00:29:48,165 --> 00:29:51,172
- Why don't you tell her?
- Let it be. She called you stupid.

407
00:29:51,524 --> 00:29:53,485
Congratulations, brother!

408
00:29:53,604 --> 00:29:57,094
The news of Rajesh's engagement
has gladdened my heart.

409
00:29:57,119 --> 00:29:59,407
I've just been to the
temple to offer my prayers.

410
00:29:59,743 --> 00:30:01,274
She's coming from the beauty parlour.

411
00:30:01,915 --> 00:30:02,814
What happened?

412
00:30:03,602 --> 00:30:04,375
Okay!

413
00:30:04,915 --> 00:30:08,728
I've heard that daughter-in-law's
dad is a professor at a college.

414
00:30:08,782 --> 00:30:09,345
Yes, right!

415
00:30:09,626 --> 00:30:11,907
In that case, there must not
have been any talks of dowry.

416
00:30:12,078 --> 00:30:16,585
He must be like him,
a simpleton all his life.

417
00:30:16,610 --> 00:30:19,704
Don't say that.
He's from a very big family.

418
00:30:19,828 --> 00:30:24,032
But he is his friend.
Whatever he gives has to be accepted.

419
00:30:24,267 --> 00:30:27,374
If my Sweetie were to come,
she would have brought a lot.

420
00:30:27,399 --> 00:30:29,554
So much that the safe wouldn't be
able to accommodate everything.

421
00:30:29,579 --> 00:30:31,030
My Rajesh is worth millions!

422
00:30:31,055 --> 00:30:34,110
Something worth millions
is being made... Sweets!

423
00:30:34,135 --> 00:30:34,468
Sweet!

424
00:30:34,493 --> 00:30:36,679
- Rita baby is making it.
- Is baby making it?

425
00:30:36,704 --> 00:30:38,571
- Will you taste it?
- Give me some.

426
00:30:38,596 --> 00:30:39,682
I'll get it, right away.

427
00:30:41,143 --> 00:30:43,336
- Baby, is the sweet ready?
- Yes!

428
00:30:43,493 --> 00:30:45,290
I've praised your sweet a lot outside.

429
00:30:45,315 --> 00:30:45,884
Really!

430
00:30:45,985 --> 00:30:48,899
Your aunt wants to die... I mean taste it.

431
00:30:48,989 --> 00:30:50,844
I'll just go and give it.

432
00:30:51,802 --> 00:30:54,493
Baby, you've learnt a lot.

433
00:30:54,609 --> 00:30:57,657
Auntie, eat with this big spoon.
Baby has made it.

434
00:30:59,563 --> 00:31:00,485
Have it.

435
00:31:09,245 --> 00:31:11,641
- What happened?
- Auntie liked the sweet a lot.

436
00:31:11,666 --> 00:31:14,346
Have all of this, auntie.

437
00:31:20,682 --> 00:31:23,477
Is this what you call sweet?
It's full of salt.

438
00:31:23,502 --> 00:31:26,111
- Salt?
- Yes. It's very bitter.

439
00:31:26,190 --> 00:31:28,463
My dear, it's your tongue that's bitter.

440
00:31:28,526 --> 00:31:29,635
- What did you say?
- Nothing.

441
00:31:29,660 --> 00:31:32,291
The girl's family is about to come.
You wipe your face.

442
00:31:32,316 --> 00:31:33,394
Yeah... okay, okay!

443
00:31:33,459 --> 00:31:37,814
Move aside with your sweet. - Rita,
you won't be able to make this sweet.

444
00:31:39,237 --> 00:31:43,604
If I can't make the sweet for
you, who can?

445
00:31:57,774 --> 00:31:59,829
Greetings! Please, come.

446
00:31:59,854 --> 00:32:01,493
Oh, Mr. Kailashnath!

447
00:32:01,518 --> 00:32:03,393
- How are you?
- May you live long!

448
00:32:04,001 --> 00:32:05,111
May you live long, son. How are you?

449
00:32:05,136 --> 00:32:05,517
Fine!

450
00:32:05,542 --> 00:32:06,260
How are you, son?

451
00:32:06,525 --> 00:32:07,861
- Hi, Nisha!
- Hi...

452
00:32:12,181 --> 00:32:12,697
Welcome!

453
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:15,941
Thanks!

454
00:32:22,895 --> 00:32:23,731
Computers!

455
00:32:24,106 --> 00:32:26,035
You're studying computers? Wow!

456
00:32:26,652 --> 00:32:29,410
Nisha... Lalloo and Chameli
have come to meet you.

457
00:32:29,435 --> 00:32:31,104
- Greetings!
- Greetings!

458
00:32:31,129 --> 00:32:34,416
Meet him, too. He happens to be the
most loved member of this family.

459
00:32:34,441 --> 00:32:36,262
- How sweet!
- He never bites.

460
00:32:37,184 --> 00:32:38,020
He only loves.

461
00:32:39,530 --> 00:32:43,785
- Brother-in-law! You show us your paintings.
- Definitely, come.

462
00:32:44,106 --> 00:32:46,644
Rajesh, please come here, dear.

463
00:32:46,957 --> 00:32:49,824
This father-in-law of yours
is a very interesting person.

464
00:32:51,144 --> 00:32:54,214
I'll just be there.
Prem, you please show Nisha the paintings.

465
00:32:54,567 --> 00:32:55,270
Wow!

466
00:32:56,559 --> 00:32:57,098
Really...

467
00:32:57,337 --> 00:32:58,439
...brother-in-law is truly great.

468
00:32:59,316 --> 00:33:00,387
This is so good!

469
00:33:01,347 --> 00:33:03,659
- And this is... beautiful!
- Beautiful!

470
00:33:04,973 --> 00:33:09,308
I'll show you the most beautiful painting
done by my brother. Please, come.

471
00:33:10,926 --> 00:33:13,363
- Chocolates?!
- Oh, chocolates! Thanks... please, come!

472
00:33:21,449 --> 00:33:22,113
How is it?

473
00:33:25,012 --> 00:33:28,192
Do you know to play the
instrument or are you just posing?

474
00:33:28,918 --> 00:33:30,481
People tell me that I play very well.

475
00:33:30,977 --> 00:33:33,933
You may make a decision, when you hear it.

476
00:33:34,402 --> 00:33:39,449
I almost forgot. Sister has sent this
gift for you. - Sister-in-law sent it?

477
00:33:39,754 --> 00:33:40,567
Wow!

478
00:33:41,057 --> 00:33:43,062
I told her that it wasn't necessary.

