Dear in-law, this heart is so crazy.

1663
02:20:12,396 --> 02:20:15,694
Whatever it gets, it always expects more!

1664
02:20:16,428 --> 02:20:18,061
The other day, we stopped you all.

1665
02:20:18,938 --> 02:20:21,733
Now, the heart once again desires
to stop you all for a day.

1666
02:20:25,647 --> 02:20:29,584
Brother, please do me a favour.
I want a photo with Nisha.

1667
02:20:30,241 --> 02:20:33,600
That would be a remembrance
of her loving stay with us.

1668
02:20:34,920 --> 02:20:37,584
- Sir, one photo for us too.
- Me too!

1669
02:20:37,609 --> 02:20:38,505
Me too!

1670
02:20:38,530 --> 02:20:41,248
All right! Prem, get the camera.

1671
02:20:52,267 --> 02:20:53,037
Are you going?

1672
02:20:57,164 --> 02:21:00,707
There's no excuse now...
so that I can stop you.

1673
02:21:06,108 --> 02:21:09,327
Can I ask you something?
Will you tell me the truth?

1674
02:21:10,511 --> 02:21:11,085
What?

1675
02:21:17,315 --> 02:21:18,402
Why did you stop me yesterday?

1676
02:21:21,662 --> 02:21:22,730
I wanted to speak to you
on a couple of topics.

1677
02:21:23,362 --> 02:21:23,832
What?

1678
02:21:25,098 --> 02:21:26,676
Immediately after the
inauguration of the factory...

1679
02:21:27,263 --> 02:21:29,042
...l'll speak to sister-in-law
about our marriage.

1680
02:21:55,369 --> 02:21:57,274
What are you all staring
at, my dear friends?

1681
02:21:57,334 --> 02:22:00,132
Our Prem is the big boss today!
Salute him!

1682
02:22:00,689 --> 02:22:02,048
- Good!
- Thank you!

1683
02:22:03,510 --> 02:22:05,876
Are you going to your
maternal place tomorrow?

1684
02:22:05,901 --> 02:22:08,650
Yes, mom and dad remember
the little one a lot.

1685
02:22:08,946 --> 02:22:10,419
- I will go with her.
- I'll go.

1686
02:22:10,459 --> 02:22:11,576
- I'll go...
- I'll go...

1687
02:22:11,604 --> 02:22:11,815
Shut up!

1688
02:22:11,840 --> 02:22:12,501
We both will go.

1689
02:22:12,526 --> 02:22:15,892
- There's a letter from your village.
- Letter from my village?

1690
02:22:16,212 --> 02:22:17,845
What does it say? Please, read it.

1691
02:22:18,862 --> 02:22:21,423
- What is written?
- Your sister-in-law is very sick.

1692
02:22:21,841 --> 02:22:23,638
She has been admitted to a hospital.

1693
02:22:23,992 --> 02:22:25,041
They've asked you to
come over immediately.

1694
02:22:25,853 --> 02:22:26,888
But...

1695
02:22:28,602 --> 02:22:29,071
Sister-in-law...

1696
02:22:29,244 --> 02:22:30,517
You make the arrangements to leave.

1697
02:22:30,568 --> 02:22:34,126
You will get the afternoon bus.
I'll make the arrangements for you to leave.

1698
02:22:38,955 --> 02:22:41,666
Who are you giving this cash to?

1699
02:22:41,856 --> 02:22:44,048
I'm giving it to Lalloo.
He'll need it for the treatment.

1700
02:22:44,266 --> 02:22:50,068
This is what I feared.
I know these servants very well.

1701
02:22:50,155 --> 02:22:54,305
- This sickness is an excuse to get some cash.
- Auntie!

1702
02:22:54,931 --> 02:22:58,114
Letters like these are
available for 5 bucks.

1703
02:22:58,234 --> 02:23:01,032
Neither will this cash
come back nor will he...

1704
02:23:04,412 --> 02:23:10,903
It was my duty to caution you.
Now it's left to you to decide. Servant!

1705
02:23:27,636 --> 02:23:28,666
Lalloo!

1706
02:23:30,365 --> 02:23:37,565
I swear! This letter is not fake.
It hasn't been bought.

1707
02:23:39,048 --> 02:23:43,015
It's a false accusation.

1708
02:23:43,282 --> 02:23:47,961
It's because I'm a small man!

1709
02:23:51,614 --> 02:23:53,003
From when have you become small?

1710
02:23:57,581 --> 02:24:00,550
You call me sister-in-law, right?

1711
02:24:01,937 --> 02:24:04,457
Keep this.

1712
02:24:04,598 --> 02:24:11,489
I'm afraid.
What if something happens to her?

1713
02:24:12,112 --> 02:24:14,659
Nothing's going to happen to her.
Come with me.

1714
02:24:34,048 --> 02:24:37,017
I'm confident that nothing
will happen to her.

1715
02:24:42,142 --> 02:24:43,243
Go!

1716
02:24:49,103 --> 02:24:50,144
Listen!

1717
02:24:51,086 --> 02:24:56,963
When she is cured,
tell her that you've found yourself a girl.

1718
02:25:07,491 --> 02:25:10,752
- So, are you leaving?
- You come along, too.

1719
02:25:12,530 --> 02:25:14,022
I'll come over to bring you back.

1720
02:25:15,358 --> 02:25:17,733
Let's go, sister-in-law!

1721
02:25:18,284 --> 02:25:20,708
Just a minute! Let us have tea, at least!

1722
02:25:20,733 --> 02:25:24,726
- There's no time for tea now.
- Give the child to me.

1723
02:25:24,904 --> 02:25:25,989
Only one chance, okay?

1724
02:25:28,440 --> 02:25:29,831
So, you're ready to go?

1725
02:25:30,871 --> 02:25:31,855
Uncle!

1726
02:25:32,621 --> 02:25:38,714
Lalloo went yesterday.
You will go today. I will be restless.

1727
02:25:38,814 --> 02:25:42,323
The work of our factory has started now.

1728
02:25:42,841 --> 02:25:44,823
Please get my brother-in-law
married and get us a companion.

1729
02:25:44,848 --> 02:25:47,948
That's great, sister-in-law!

1730
02:25:47,979 --> 02:25:48,793
A sister-in-law should be like this.

1731
02:25:48,794 --> 02:25:51,284
Did you see that, Rajesh? What times!

1732
02:25:52,066 --> 02:25:56,105
Daughter-in-law, it's your responsibility
now to find a bride for him.

1733
02:25:56,191 --> 02:25:57,238
I love you, sister-in-law!

1734
02:26:01,800 --> 02:26:03,277
What's the matter, brother-in-law?

1735
02:26:03,418 --> 02:26:05,620
I'm going to my maternal place
and you are the one who's excited.

1736
02:26:05,840 --> 02:26:08,886
One word about your marriage and
the weather seems transformed!

1737
02:26:08,911 --> 02:26:10,238
Yes, sister-in-law! I love you!

1738
02:26:10,615 --> 02:26:12,822
Let's talk something serious now.

1739
02:26:13,027 --> 02:26:15,543
Uncle has given me your
responsibility now.

1740
02:26:15,647 --> 02:26:19,042
Tell me, would you like a love
marriage or an arranged marriage?

1741
02:26:19,218 --> 02:26:22,894
Sister-in-law, a love marriage
that you have to arrange.

1742
02:26:23,503 --> 02:26:25,636
- What?
- I love you, sister-in-law!

1743
02:26:28,299 --> 02:26:31,510
Did you see that, son?
Your uncle is smarter than your dad!

1744
02:26:32,019 --> 02:26:33,886
He has already found an auntie for you.

1745
02:26:34,269 --> 02:26:38,198
Even he likes his auntie.
He has seen the photo.

1746
02:26:38,273 --> 02:26:40,183
What do you say, little one? Say, yes.

1747
02:26:42,214 --> 02:26:43,652
Show me the photo, too.

1748
02:26:44,227 --> 02:26:46,597
You talk about photo,
I'll show you her face itself.

1749
02:26:46,972 --> 02:26:48,769
So, is the destination
of your love on the way?

1750
02:26:48,927 --> 02:26:51,808
It's on the way,
sister-in-law, on the way.

1751
02:27:01,826 --> 02:27:04,870
My destination has
arrived but where's yours?

1752
02:27:05,105 --> 02:27:07,519
Sister-in-law, the destination
of both of us is the same.

1753
02:27:10,355 --> 02:27:11,407
Nisha!

1754
02:27:16,761 --> 02:27:18,058
Welcome, sister-in-law!

1755
02:27:18,339 --> 02:27:19,355
Hey!

1756
02:27:19,444 --> 02:27:20,629
Come on in.

1757
02:27:21,332 --> 02:27:23,253
Sister-in-law, have a seat.
Think of it as your own home!

1758
02:27:23,278 --> 02:27:25,433
- What is all this?
- You read this first.

1759
02:27:27,224 --> 02:27:30,252
'Mom and dad have gone out.'
- 'Won't return till evening.'

1760
02:27:30,277 --> 02:27:31,831
'You have your breakfast-Nisha!'

1761
02:27:32,371 --> 02:27:37,503
I got it! You and your madam
have pre-arranged this program.

1762
02:27:38,150 --> 02:27:41,605
What love!
Call up your brother at the office.

1763
02:27:41,630 --> 02:27:44,105
Why? - Let me give him the good news too.

1764
02:27:44,800 --> 02:27:46,784
- Sister-in-law, where are your feet?
- Call up!

1765
02:27:49,621 --> 02:27:50,199
Hello!

1766
02:27:50,519 --> 02:27:54,332
- Is brother in?
- No. He's gone out for some important work.

1767
02:27:54,510 --> 02:27:56,222
- Gone out?
- Leave a message.

1768
02:27:56,254 --> 02:27:59,144
Tell him to call up sister-in-law,
as soon as he returns. - Yes.

1769
02:28:01,005 --> 02:28:05,611
Now, please get up.
Put this on Nisha in front of me.

1770
02:28:05,636 --> 02:28:09,248
Sister-in-law, how can I? Your sister
is so shy that she's not coming down.

1771
02:28:09,743 --> 02:28:14,175
If she's not coming down, we'll go to her.

1772
02:28:15,557 --> 02:28:18,409
We're from the boy's side.
We'll take along the marriage procession.

1773
02:28:21,144 --> 02:28:23,389
"I'm going..."

1774
02:28:25,406 --> 02:28:31,937
"I'm going with my brother-in-law's
marriage procession."

1775
02:28:34,204 --> 02:28:40,165
"I'm going with my brother-in-law's
marriage procession."

1776
02:28:40,548 --> 02:28:45,793
"No music, nobody else,
only the message of happiness"

1777
02:28:45,864 --> 02:28:52,239
"I'm going with my brother-in-law's
marriage procession."

1778
02:29:06,763 --> 02:29:11,770
"Brother-in-law becomes the groom
and wears the turban on the head."

1779
02:29:12,667 --> 02:29:17,122
"Sister-in-law gives him her blessings."

1780
02:29:19,979 --> 02:29:24,939
"The buds of love blossom and
we get happiness all the time."

1781
02:29:25,797 --> 02:29:30,403
"I bless you from the bottom of my heart."

1782
02:29:31,647 --> 02:29:36,942
"Astride a horse,
this groom goes to get his bride"

1783
02:29:36,967 --> 02:29:39,223
"I'm going..."

1784
02:29:41,372 --> 02:29:47,450
"I'm going with my brother-in-law's
marriage procession."

1785
02:29:53,418 --> 02:29:58,378
"That's great Lord!
What a pair you have created!"

1786
02:29:59,122 --> 02:30:03,942
"Brother-in-law and sister-in-law...
congratulations!"

1787
02:30:05,153 --> 02:30:08,066
"More than any other
ritual in this world..."

1788
02:30:08,091 --> 02:30:10,762
"...the relation of hearts
is the most important!"

1789
02:30:13,945 --> 02:30:19,012
"The all-important moment has arrived."

1790
02:30:19,763 --> 02:30:24,262
"Till yesterday, I was the only
daughter-in-law of the house."

1791
02:30:27,060 --> 02:30:31,989
"I will command and I will stare too."

1792
02:30:32,877 --> 02:30:37,465
"And she'll just watch with awe."

1793
02:30:38,681 --> 02:30:43,864
"I come with a thousand dreams"

1794
02:30:43,889 --> 02:30:46,366
"I'm going..."

1795
02:30:48,468 --> 02:30:54,972
"I'm going with my brother-in-law's
marriage procession"

1796
02:31:12,167 --> 02:31:15,136
It must be his phone.
Nisha, please take care of him.

1797
02:31:37,698 --> 02:31:38,261
Sister-in-law!

1798
02:32:50,995 --> 02:32:54,691
Doctor, she's trying to say something.

1799
02:33:08,497 --> 02:33:09,855
Injection Atropine, quick!

1800
02:33:30,090 --> 02:33:32,582
Please do something, doctor.

1801
02:33:53,894 --> 02:33:54,720
What's the matter, doctor?

1802
02:33:57,689 --> 02:33:58,283
I'm sorry!

1803
02:34:59,483 --> 02:35:04,443
Have it, Tuffy! The one who used
to feed you won't be coming!

1804
02:35:06,005 --> 02:35:11,223
She was here only for a few
days to distribute her love.

1805
02:35:12,723 --> 02:35:13,779
Have it, dear!

1806
02:35:16,755 --> 02:35:19,809
Be brave, brother.

1807
02:35:20,395 --> 02:35:24,667
Wonder what magic she had!
Without her, we've forgotten to live!

1808
02:35:25,700 --> 02:35:27,224
We've forgotten to live, doctor!

1809
02:35:34,817 --> 02:35:36,785
Hey, brother. Stop!

1810
02:35:38,474 --> 02:35:41,661
How are you, brother? Take this cash.

1811
02:35:41,942 --> 02:35:43,903
Brother, a miracle
occurred a few days back.

1812
02:35:44,575 --> 02:35:46,099
Jagan... Jagan!

1813
02:35:46,731 --> 02:35:51,082
All the doctors had given up.
They said that she wouldn't survive.

1814
02:35:51,505 --> 02:35:55,606
But I had faith that
nothing could happen to her.

1815
02:35:56,640 --> 02:35:58,608
After all, my sister-in-law
Pooja had prayed for her!

1816
02:35:58,690 --> 02:36:01,153
And that's what happened.
She opened her eyes and smiled.

1817
02:36:01,429 --> 02:36:06,230
I told her that it's because of
my sister-in-law's blessings.

1818
02:36:07,737 --> 02:36:12,223
I'd like to give this good
news to my sister-in-law.

1819
02:36:21,571 --> 02:36:25,286
That blessing which was over
us has been snatched from us.

1820
02:36:52,610 --> 02:36:55,463
Big brother, what happened?

1821
02:36:56,932 --> 02:36:58,188
What has happened, big brother?

1822
02:36:59,437 --> 02:37:05,398
Sir, she gave up her life
for the sake of my tears!

1823
02:37:06,694 --> 02:37:12,408
She blessed and gave the gift
of life to my own sister-in-law.

1824
02:37:15,954 --> 02:37:21,596
Big brother, do ask God as to why
he takes away all the good people.

1825
02:37:22,390 --> 02:37:25,947
Why does he call them?
Ask him, big brother.

1826
02:37:27,010 --> 02:37:29,096
Laloo, your sister-in-law
Pooja was a goddess of love!

1827
02:37:29,851 --> 02:37:31,648
She was so full of love and care!

1828
02:37:33,259 --> 02:37:38,660
He is hungry for love, too!
He needs love, too!

1829
02:37:40,971 --> 02:37:41,495
Uncle!

1830
02:37:42,377 --> 02:37:45,416
The love and care that you talk about...

1831
02:37:46,251 --> 02:37:49,471
...that was rightfully
due to our little one.

1832
02:37:50,846 --> 02:37:52,814
What will happen of him now?

1833
02:37:54,656 --> 02:37:58,036
Big brother, what will
happen of our little one now?

1834
02:37:58,679 --> 02:38:02,479
Big brother, tell me,
what will happen of our little one?

1835
02:38:23,051 --> 02:38:25,151
Go child, go and put him
to sleep in his place.

1836
02:38:25,925 --> 02:38:26,284
Yes!

1837
02:38:36,527 --> 02:38:38,815
- Is the child asleep?
- He's trying to sleep.

1838
02:38:41,245 --> 02:38:44,323
He considers his auntie's
lap to be his mother's.

1839
02:38:52,889 --> 02:38:57,307
After Pooja's departure,
when we miss her so much...

1840
02:38:58,527 --> 02:39:00,331
...just think of Rajesh's plight.

1841
02:39:20,306 --> 02:39:25,266
Rajesh is not very well.
He may not say a word...

1842
02:39:26,219 --> 02:39:28,358
...but we have been observing
him for the past few days.

1843
02:39:29,668 --> 02:39:36,209
He is mentally disturbed thinking
of the welfare of the child.

1844
02:39:36,404 --> 02:39:40,811
- But doctor, what is the cure?
- There is a cure.

1845
02:39:42,876 --> 02:39:46,881
Brother, we have to set
up his life once again.

1846
02:39:50,532 --> 02:39:54,998
Professor... 'This is the way of
life that can't go unnoticed...

1847
02:39:56,624 --> 02:39:59,990
...the breath stops but life goes on!'

1848
02:40:02,271 --> 02:40:06,537
For a child, the shadow of
a mother is very important.

1849
02:40:06,863 --> 02:40:09,576
I'd say, at an appropriate moment,
do speak to Rajesh about it.

1850
02:40:10,031 --> 02:40:13,193
Please drop me to the dispensary.
I'll give Rajesh's medicines too.

1851
02:40:14,306 --> 02:40:15,326
I'll leave, professor.

1852
02:40:19,951 --> 02:40:22,920
The doctor was absolutely right.

1853
02:40:23,443 --> 02:40:29,889
Rajesh, you need not
worry about your child.

1854
02:40:30,135 --> 02:40:32,021
Do heed my advice and remarry.

1855
02:40:33,425 --> 02:40:37,217
You haven't aged!
You will still get a lot of proposals.

1856
02:40:38,047 --> 02:40:41,490
Well, my Sweetie is all ready
for marriage even today.

1857
02:40:42,350 --> 02:40:45,435
If Rajesh had got married to Sweetie...

1858
02:40:45,621 --> 02:40:47,678
...we would have been spared
the agony of this day.

1859
02:40:47,881 --> 02:40:48,529
Bhagvanti!

1860
02:40:48,686 --> 02:40:49,522
You better be quiet!

1861
02:40:50,313 --> 02:40:52,857
Rajesh, my child,
I have already spoken to Sweetie.

1862
02:40:53,137 --> 02:40:56,608
She has only one condition.
The maid will look after the child.

1863
02:40:56,724 --> 02:40:57,170
What?

1864
02:40:57,999 --> 02:41:00,193
- Will a maid look after the child?
- Yes.

1865
02:41:00,829 --> 02:41:08,341
Big brother, I beg of you. Don't hand
over our little one to such a woman...

1866
02:41:08,433 --> 02:41:10,208
...who doesn't know the
meaning of the word 'mother'.

1867
02:41:10,241 --> 02:41:13,107
- You don't interfere!
- Lalloo is right.

1868
02:41:13,951 --> 02:41:16,865
This choice of yours doesn't
have the qualities of a mother.

1869
02:41:17,322 --> 02:41:21,873
To love somebody else's child,
one needs to understand one's customs.

1870
02:41:21,898 --> 02:41:22,615
Do you understand?

1871
02:41:22,654 --> 02:41:23,113
Look!

1872
02:41:23,138 --> 02:41:25,459
Sister-in-law, he is right.

1873
02:41:25,537 --> 02:41:28,568
He's talking a lot of rubbish
and affronting my niece.

1874
02:41:28,610 --> 02:41:31,091
Which girl would like to be a step mom?

1875
02:41:31,123 --> 02:41:33,662
Which parents would hand
over her daughter to Rajesh?

1876
02:41:33,711 --> 02:41:35,412
Forgive me, I'd like to ask you...

1877
02:41:35,437 --> 02:41:37,271
...will you get your
Nisha married to Rajesh?

1878
02:41:38,779 --> 02:41:39,584
Bhagvanti!

1879
02:41:40,365 --> 02:41:41,412
Stop it. That's enough now.

1880
02:41:41,463 --> 02:41:45,935
You be quiet.
Keep the lectures for your college.

1881
02:41:46,326 --> 02:41:50,051
I ask you, what's the harm in the
condition laid down by Sweetie?

1882
02:41:50,076 --> 02:41:52,874
All this argument for
the sake of a mere child.

1883
02:41:52,915 --> 02:41:55,795
How does it matter? Children do grow up.

1884
02:41:55,820 --> 02:41:56,537
Bhagvanti!

1885
02:42:01,045 --> 02:42:01,631
Disgusting!

1886
02:42:05,142 --> 02:42:09,787
This nature of yours might be
responsible for us to be childless.

1887
02:42:17,761 --> 02:42:20,566
I'm sorry... sorry!

1888
02:42:25,925 --> 02:42:26,660
No, uncle!

1889
02:42:27,944 --> 02:42:29,912
I don't want a step mom for my son.

1890
02:42:31,518 --> 02:42:34,487
All the step moms aren't necessarily bad.

1891
02:42:34,751 --> 02:42:38,386
- Brother!
- No, Prem. I won't marry again.

1892
02:42:41,661 --> 02:42:42,386
Come in, professor.

1893
02:42:46,557 --> 02:42:48,525
Rajesh isn't ready to marry.

1894
02:42:50,544 --> 02:42:56,605
He is right too. How can he hand
over his cherished one to a stranger?

1895
02:42:57,708 --> 02:43:05,183
Dad, for my son and me,
Pooja's thoughts would suffice!

1896
02:43:06,631 --> 02:43:09,714
But, someday,
you will have to get married.

1897
02:43:11,870 --> 02:43:14,619
Today, we all are there to
take care of the little one.

1898
02:43:15,082 --> 02:43:19,824
His grandfather, grandmother...
but we won't be there always!

1899
02:43:21,414 --> 02:43:23,798
In life, at every step, one needs support.

1900
02:43:24,996 --> 02:43:29,923
And then, bringing up a child
is a major responsibility.

1901
02:43:31,592 --> 02:43:33,928
But chances are that my
son might get such a mom...

1902
02:43:35,142 --> 02:43:36,772
...who might ignore him in the future.

1903
02:43:38,325 --> 02:43:42,827
For him, the mother that
would come would be his own.

1904
02:43:43,956 --> 02:43:49,748
Kailashnath, what if Nisha comes
into this house in place of Pooja?

1905
02:43:54,044 --> 02:43:56,889
From the time she's gone from here,
she's been talking about this place.

1906
02:43:57,704 --> 02:43:59,678
The child too is in her
care throughout the day.

1907
02:44:01,857 --> 02:44:04,709
Get married to Nisha, Rajesh.
In these conditions...

1908
02:44:04,734 --> 02:44:08,897
...if anyone can take the place of his
mom, it would be his auntie.

1909
02:44:50,729 --> 02:44:52,816
What do you have to say, Prem?

1910
02:44:54,639 --> 02:44:58,746
- Please do agree brother.
- The child will get a mom.

1911
02:45:00,669 --> 02:45:01,866
Please ask Nisha, first.

1912
02:45:05,532 --> 02:45:10,183
I deemed it right and spoke
about Nisha to Kailashnath.

1913
02:45:12,465 --> 02:45:14,308
If Nisha goes into that
house as a daughter-in-law...

1914
02:45:15,175 --> 02:45:17,504
...and brightens up
Pooja's house once again.

1915
02:45:18,770 --> 02:45:20,996
I don't think we can ask for
any happiness greater than that.

1916
02:45:24,588 --> 02:45:31,590
I'll ask Nisha and if she agrees
we'll get her married with fanfare.

1917
02:45:35,044 --> 02:45:40,074
Due to Pooja's absence,
we must not be found lacking in any way.

1918
02:45:44,268 --> 02:45:45,280
You...

1919
02:45:47,473 --> 02:45:48,562
Nisha!

1920
02:45:52,340 --> 02:45:52,949
Nisha!

1921
02:45:56,738 --> 02:45:57,832
What is your wish, my child?

1922
02:45:58,962 --> 02:45:59,910
Whatever you'll deem fit.

1923
02:46:04,722 --> 02:46:06,153
I'll just call up Kailashnath.

1924
02:46:07,574 --> 02:46:08,434
PROF. CHOWDHURY: Hello, Kailashnath!

1925
02:46:09,410 --> 02:46:10,527
Nisha has agreed.

1926
02:46:11,001 --> 02:46:14,614
I'll call up the priest today and find
an auspicious date for the marriage.

1927
02:46:15,848 --> 02:46:16,932
That's true.

1928
02:46:18,004 --> 02:46:19,137
Yes, absolutely!

1929
02:46:51,903 --> 02:46:57,528
"O mother, the crow on your
roof foretells that..."

1930
02:46:57,553 --> 02:47:00,345
"...your darling daughter
has renounced this house..."

1931
02:47:00,377 --> 02:47:02,564
"...and has fallen in
love with a stranger!"

1932
02:47:02,629 --> 02:47:05,090
Welcome, Kailashnath. Welcome, son.

1933
02:47:05,848 --> 02:47:06,856
Are you through with the preparations?

1934
02:47:06,881 --> 02:47:08,184
Yes, the cards have already been printed.

1935
02:47:08,606 --> 02:47:10,403
We'd gone to Ramtekdi for blessings.

1936
02:47:10,451 --> 02:47:12,248
Thought that we'd meet the little one too.

1937
02:47:14,020 --> 02:47:15,988
- Where is our little one?
- He's upstairs in Nisha's room.

1938
02:47:16,356 --> 02:47:18,254
- Child, please go and get the little one.
- I'll do that.

1939
02:47:18,726 --> 02:47:21,363
How is Nisha? - She's fine.
She's applying henna on her hands.

1940
02:47:25,395 --> 02:47:27,777
Sister, auntie has asked me to
bring the little one downstairs.

1941
02:47:27,858 --> 02:47:30,073
- May I take him?
- Yes. Be careful.

1942
02:47:30,395 --> 02:47:31,239
Don't worry!

1943
02:47:31,606 --> 02:47:37,043
Just have a look at what I have in my hand.
Her wedding card.

1944
02:47:38,028 --> 02:47:39,317
Please, read it.

1945
02:47:40,468 --> 02:47:44,699
'By the grace of God the
marriage of our daughter Nisha...

1946
02:47:44,724 --> 02:47:48,746
...has been fixed with
Rajesh.' 'You are welcome...'

1947
02:47:49,010 --> 02:47:51,075
- What are you reading? Read properly.
- I'm reading properly.

1948
02:47:51,685 --> 02:47:55,953
'By the grace of God the
marriage of our daughter Nisha...

1949
02:47:55,978 --> 02:48:01,629
...has been fixed with Rajesh.
You are welcome to bless the couple.'

1950
02:48:01,741 --> 02:48:03,293
- Give it to me.
- What happened?

1951
02:48:13,528 --> 02:48:18,622
"O mother, the crow on your
roof foretells that..."

1952
02:48:18,816 --> 02:48:21,367
"...your darling daughter
has renounced this house..."

1953
02:48:21,392 --> 02:48:23,719
"...and has fallen in
love with a stranger!"

1954
02:48:29,867 --> 02:48:34,671
"You had taken a religious
vow for my wedding..."

1955
02:48:35,406 --> 02:48:40,578
"...now you should get me
engaged with that sage."

1956
02:48:40,953 --> 02:48:44,609
"Apply henna on these hands."

1957
02:48:46,490 --> 02:48:49,140
"Apply henna on these hands..."

1958
02:48:49,211 --> 02:48:51,992
"...and tie the auspicious
thread of the ritual."

1959
02:48:52,059 --> 02:48:54,894
Uncle... this...

1960
02:48:54,934 --> 02:48:56,426
Nisha!

1961
02:48:57,895 --> 02:48:58,457
Nisha!

1962
02:48:58,748 --> 02:49:02,402
You've done us a big favour by
agreeing to get married to Rajesh.

1963
02:49:05,183 --> 02:49:07,809
You have given a new lease
of life to two people.

1964
02:49:08,762 --> 02:49:09,621
You've given them a new life.

1965
02:49:10,438 --> 02:49:11,004
See!

1966
02:49:31,582 --> 02:49:32,340
Nisha!

1967
02:49:32,613 --> 02:49:35,823
- What happened?
- She was all right, just now.

1968
02:49:35,848 --> 02:49:36,942
Please, call some doctor.

1969
02:49:37,325 --> 02:49:38,739
- Nisha!
- Child...

1970
02:49:40,521 --> 02:49:44,480
She's perfectly all right.
I've given her an injection.

1971
02:49:44,763 --> 02:49:45,824
She'll be conscious very soon.

1972
02:49:45,849 --> 02:49:49,488
- Doctor, how come, all of a sudden...
- It's a matter of marriage...

1973
02:49:49,565 --> 02:49:51,362
...must have felt giddy
due to the exertion.

1974
02:49:51,557 --> 02:49:54,504
Don't be afraid, professor.
I'll take your leave.

1975
02:49:54,590 --> 02:49:55,332
- Bhola...
- Yes...

1976
02:49:55,496 --> 02:49:57,863
Thank God. We'll take your leave too.

1977
02:49:58,417 --> 02:50:01,011
- Okay, little one!
- Come here...

1978
02:50:02,809 --> 02:50:04,129
- Good bye!
- Good bye!

1979
02:50:05,184 --> 02:50:08,067
Mom, I'd like to meet Nisha for once.

1980
02:50:08,092 --> 02:50:10,551
- Come.
- Not now. I don't want to disturb her.

1981
02:50:11,057 --> 02:50:12,916
- Please, give her this letter.
- Okay!

1982
02:50:39,361 --> 02:50:42,572
RAJESH: Nisha, the step that you've
taken for the sake of the little one...

1983
02:50:43,033 --> 02:50:44,713
...l'm grateful to you for that.

1984
02:50:45,673 --> 02:50:47,439
Everyone is very happy with this decision.

1985
02:50:48,387 --> 02:50:53,400
But I know that every girl has
her own dreams, her own ambitions.

1986
02:50:54,581 --> 02:50:59,673
Nisha, if there is something in your
heart, please let me know.

1987
02:51:00,407 --> 02:51:04,400
Nothing is greater than
your happiness. Rajesh.

1988
02:51:35,300 --> 02:51:36,306
Hello!

1989
02:51:40,032 --> 02:51:40,513
Who?

1990
02:51:52,982 --> 02:51:58,918
"I will erase the memories
of love from my heart."

1991
02:51:59,270 --> 02:52:05,207
"For the sake of my responsibilities,
I will forget everything."

1992
02:52:11,895 --> 02:52:17,731
"The responsibilities that
you have to live up to!"

1993
02:52:18,192 --> 02:52:23,887
"How will I repay you for this favour?"

1994
02:52:24,434 --> 02:52:30,473
"As a mark of respect,
I bow in front of you."

1995
02:52:30,801 --> 02:52:37,058
"As a mark of respect,
I bow in front of you"

1996
02:53:39,414 --> 02:53:41,172
Auntie, let me hold my nephew.

1997
02:53:41,606 --> 02:53:43,452
Come to your uncle, my dear.

1998
02:53:43,625 --> 02:53:44,203
Go!

1999
02:53:47,859 --> 02:53:48,594
Come, child.

2000
02:54:03,622 --> 02:54:09,934
Oh God, what troubled times are we facing?

2001
02:54:15,525 --> 02:54:17,700
Prem brother has taken an
oath from me not to speak out.

2002
02:54:18,521 --> 02:54:19,627
He's made me helpless.

2003
02:54:20,848 --> 02:54:28,945
But you aren't helpless.
Oh God, work out such a miracle today...

2004
02:54:28,970 --> 02:54:35,825
...so that your devotees
trust you all the more.

2005
02:54:36,115 --> 02:54:36,779
O God!

2006
02:56:41,058 --> 02:56:46,559
'Prem, my sister strengthened
our love with this necklace.'

2007
02:56:47,707 --> 02:56:49,715
'She wished that her brother-in-law's
wife should wear this necklace.'

2008
02:56:50,694 --> 02:56:52,902
'I'm returning it. Nisha.'

2009
02:57:10,321 --> 02:57:15,790
Tuffy, please do me a favour.
Please give this to Prem.

2010
02:57:38,947 --> 02:57:40,315
Please come, Rajesh.

2011
02:58:28,312 --> 02:58:29,355
Tuffy!

2012
02:58:41,387 --> 02:58:46,465
NISHA: Prem, my sister strengthened
our love with this necklace.

2013
02:58:47,314 --> 02:58:49,379
She wished that her brother-in-law's
wife should wear this necklace.

2014
02:58:50,684 --> 02:58:52,926
I'm returning it. Nisha.

2015
02:59:13,904 --> 02:59:14,544
RAJESH: Nisha!

2016
02:59:44,995 --> 02:59:45,847
What is this, Nisha?

2017
03:00:03,851 --> 03:00:07,810
Did you see Pooja,
what the two of them were about to do?

2018
03:00:12,164 --> 03:00:15,891
What would I've done?
If they had taken this step.

2019
03:00:18,741 --> 03:00:22,700
What's the matter, Rajesh?
Why did you come up all of a sudden?

2020
03:00:22,988 --> 03:00:27,948
Please read this and tell
me if this is justice.

2021
03:00:58,038 --> 03:01:00,730
Uncle, this cherished one of yours...

2022
03:01:02,009 --> 03:01:04,293
...one who used to come to me
for the smallest of advice!

2023
03:01:05,896 --> 03:01:07,949
Today, hiding such a momentous
thing in his heart...

2024
03:01:10,158 --> 03:01:11,371
...keeping it behind the
facade of his smile...

2025
03:01:13,624 --> 03:01:15,293
...he has made me a stranger!

2026
03:01:18,159 --> 03:01:20,871
Prem, what you did isn't right.

2027
03:01:25,144 --> 03:01:26,158
Mom!

2028
03:01:26,925 --> 03:01:30,129
After Pooja's departure,
I had only one wish.

2029
03:01:31,790 --> 03:01:33,808
That my child never misses his mother.

2030
03:01:36,318 --> 03:01:40,949
I ask of you Nisha,
if you had accepted him as an auntie...

2031
03:01:41,699 --> 03:01:43,442
...would your motherly
love have been reduced?

2032
03:01:44,584 --> 03:01:46,933
Tell me, Nisha. Tell me.

2033
03:01:47,564 --> 03:01:50,261
Why are you quiet, Nisha? Answer me!

2034
03:01:59,146 --> 03:02:02,988
You fool! Were you out to sacrifice
your entire life and happiness?

2035
03:02:08,167 --> 03:02:11,918
Rajesh, you should be proud of them.

2036
03:02:13,137 --> 03:02:16,824
Whatever they did, they did it
considering it to be their duty.

2037
03:02:17,790 --> 03:02:19,758
I too have a duty now.

2038
03:02:21,683 --> 03:02:22,878
Pooja's incomplete dream!

2039
03:02:24,554 --> 03:02:26,522
Actually, it was my fault.

2040
03:02:27,831 --> 03:02:35,394
I couldn't understand what you were
trying to tell me... while departing.

2041
03:02:38,091 --> 03:02:42,262
Dad, I have a request.

2042
03:02:43,784 --> 03:02:46,262
Please get Nisha married to Prem.

2043
03:02:49,433 --> 03:02:50,324
Kailashnath!

2044
03:02:52,075 --> 03:02:54,191
I might have done some good
deeds in my last birth!

2045
03:02:58,080 --> 03:03:02,472
I'm blessed by getting such sons-in-law!

2046
03:03:16,548 --> 03:03:18,844
"We all admire you today!"

2047
03:03:57,633 --> 03:04:01,564
"I'm so full of happiness!"

2048
03:04:01,682 --> 03:04:06,885
"What else can my heart ask for?"

2049
03:04:06,916 --> 03:04:11,617
"I've got everything that
I could ever ask for!"
